Figure 4(b) shows the variation of μ with temperature and VG, estimated in positive VDS regime. We observe that mobilities increase with temperature up to ~280 K, consistent with charge transport limited by impurity scattering15,26. Beyond ~280 K, the decrease in mobility with an increase in temperature can be explained on the basis of phonon scattering15,26. After fitting the mobility curves in the high temperature range according to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
